HEADWORD: hyperspace
<hw>hy"per*space</hw> <pr>(h⟦imac⟧"p⟦etil⟧r*sp⟦amac⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>hyper-</ets> + <ets>space</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A mathematical space having more than three
dimensions. It is a mathematical construct and is not intended to
represent the structure of the common physical space in which matter
exists.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

